"Zhou Z., Wu W.B.","Local linear quantile estimation for nonstationary time series",2009,"Annals of Statistics","37","5 B",,"2696","2729",,,10.1214/08-AOS636,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-69149110260&partnerID=40&md5=059f8b725f3df9a2b5a78a89472b39c6","Department of Statistics, University of Chicago, 5734 S. University Avenue, Chicago, IL 60637, United States","Zhou, Z., Department of Statistics, University of Chicago, 5734 S. University Avenue, Chicago, IL 60637, United States; Wu, W.B., Department of Statistics, University of Chicago, 5734 S. University Avenue, Chicago, IL 60637, United States","We consider estimation of quantile curves for a general class of nonstationary processes. Consistency and central limit results are obtained for local linear quantile estimates under a mild short-range dependence condition. Our results are applied to environmental data sets. In particular, our results can be used to address the problem of whether climate variability has changed, an important problem raised by IPCC (Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change) in 2001. ©Institute of Mathematical Statistics, 2009.","Bahadur representation; Climate change; Global warming; Local linear regression; Local stationarity; Nonstationary nonlinear time series; Quantile estimation; Smoothing",,,,,,,"Abberger, K., Quantile smoothing methods in financial time series (1997) Statist. Papers, 28, pp. 125-148. , MR1475190; Abberger, K., Heiler, S., Nonparametric quantile regression with applications to financial time series (2002) Statistical Data Analysis Based on the Ll-Norm and Related Methods, pp. 149-160. , (Y. Dodge, ed). Birkhäuser, Basel MR2001311; Babu, G.J., Strong representations for LAD estimators in linear models (1989) Probab. Theory Related Fields, 83, pp. 547-558. , MR1022629; Bahadur, R.R., A note on quantiles in large samples (1966) Ann. Math. Statist, 37, pp. 577-580. , MR0189095; Bai, Z.D., Rao, C.R., Wu, Y., M-estimation of multivariate linear regress